========================================
OSI MODEL – 7 LAYERS QUICK NOTES
========================================

🔹 What is OSI Model?
- Open Systems Interconnection (OSI)
- Conceptual model for network communication
- Divides communication into 7 layers
- Each layer has a specific role
- Helps in design, debugging, and standardization

Data Flow:
Sender → Layer 7 → ... → Layer 1 → Network → Layer 1 → ... → Layer 7 → Receiver

--------------------------------------------------

🔹 7 Layers (Top → Bottom)

7) Application Layer
- Closest to user
- Interface for applications

Examples:
- HTTP, FTP, SMTP

Function:
- User interaction with network

--------------------------------------------------

6) Presentation Layer
- Data formatting & transformation

Functions:
- Encryption / Decryption
- Compression
- Data format conversion

--------------------------------------------------

5) Session Layer
- Manages connection/session

Functions:
- Start / maintain / end sessions
- Checkpoints, recovery

--------------------------------------------------

4) Transport Layer
- End-to-end communication

Protocols:
- TCP (reliable)
- UDP (fast)

Functions:
- Segmentation
- Flow control
- Error handling

--------------------------------------------------

3) Network Layer
- Logical addressing & routing

Protocols:
- IP

Functions:
- Path selection
- Packet routing

--------------------------------------------------

2) Data Link Layer
- Node-to-node communication

Functions:
- Framing
- MAC addressing
- Error detection

Example:
- Ethernet

--------------------------------------------------

1) Physical Layer
- Hardware layer

Functions:
- Transmits raw bits (0/1)
- Electrical signals, cables, wireless

--------------------------------------------------

🔹 Layer Grouping

Upper Layers (5–7):
- Application-related (user interaction)

Middle Layer (4):
- Transport (reliability)

Lower Layers (1–3):
- Network + hardware transmission

--------------------------------------------------

🔹 Key Concepts

- Each layer serves the one above it
- Data encapsulation at each layer
- Abstraction simplifies complexity
- Helps isolate issues (debugging)

--------------------------------------------------

🔹 Mnemonic (Top → Bottom)

"All People Seem To Need Data Processing"

A → Application
P → Presentation
S → Session
T → Transport
N → Network
D → Data Link
P → Physical

--------------------------------------------------

🔹 Common Interview Points

- OSI is a reference model (not exact implementation)
- TCP/IP model is used in real systems
- Layers help in troubleshooting:
  - L1 → cables issue
  - L3 → routing issue
  - L7 → API issue

--------------------------------------------------

🧠 One-liner:
OSI model divides network communication into 7 layers to simplify design, communication, and troubleshooting.